            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p>Καὶ τοῦτο τὸ <expan><abbr>χαριέστ</abbr><ex>ατον</ex></expan> ἔργον <lb/>τοῦ
                    ἐνβόλου ἐγένετο ἐπὶ τοῦ <lb/>αὐτοῦ
                        <expan><abbr>θεοφιλ</abbr><ex>εστάτου</ex></expan> ἀββᾶ Θεοδώρου
                        <lb/>ἐλέ<supplied reason="omitted">ει</supplied> Θεοῦ
                            <expan><abbr>διακό</abbr><ex>νου</ex></expan> μοναχ<supplied
                        reason="omitted">οῦ</supplied> καὶ
                        <expan><abbr>ἡγουμ</abbr><ex>ένου</ex></expan>
                    <lb/>ἡ ψήφωσις αὕτη ἐν <expan><abbr>μη</abbr><ex>νὶ</ex></expan> Πανήμο<supplied
                        reason="omitted">υ</supplied>
                    <num value="12">βιʹ</num> τ<supplied reason="lost">οῦ</supplied>
                    <num value="638">ηλχʹ</num> ἔτους
                        <expan><abbr>ἰνδ</abbr><ex>ικτιῶνος</ex></expan>
                    <num value="11">αιʹ</num></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Also, the superb work of this aisle was done in the time of the most God-beloved
                    Abba (Father) Theodore the deacon, monk, and hegumen by the grace of God. This
                    mosaic (was made) on the 12th of the month of Panemos, year 638, indiction 11
                    (era of Gaza = 578). </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>"Cohen posits that the church should be associated with the town of Orda from the
                    Madaba Map mosaic."</p>
            </div>
